    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Geofroy</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward.</persName>— Received May 26, 1864</head>
                <opener>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of France to the United
                                    States.</hi>
                    </placeName>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1864-05-26">[May 26,
                                1864]</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. de Geofroy presents his compliments to Mr* Seward, and begs him to be
                            so good as to obtain from the Department of War an answer to his note of
                            the 2d of March last, relative to Mr. Cauvet, irregularly enrolled in
                            the federal army.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
            </div>
